The paper deals with image generation and spatial transformations, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms also suggests a possible fit with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the proposed method to video animation and view synthesis suggests a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM).
